\begin_layout Section*
Post-processing analysis
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
ThunderSTORM provides a variety of post-processing methods and tools which
 can be applied to the results obtained from previously processed SMLM data.
 The software includes methods for correcting the data by removing molecules
 with, e.g., poor localization accuracy, for merging molecules present in
 subsequent images, and for position correction of molecules caused by lateral
 drift of the sample and/or by axial stage scanning.
 Users can also define the order in which the different post-processing
 steps are applied.
 Localization results can be imported/exported to/from ThunderSTORM in a
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

variety of data formats which allows full compatibility with other SMLM
 localization software.
\end_layout

